## Migration to typed storage config resources

Per-backend resources with a flatter schema are replacing the generic `yba_storage_config_resource`. Migrate to the matching typed resource for your `name`:

| Old `name` | New resource |
|---|---|
| `S3` | [`yba_s3_storage_config`](s3_storage_config) |
| `GCS` | [`yba_gcs_storage_config`](gcs_storage_config) |
| `AZ` | [`yba_azure_storage_config`](azure_storage_config) |
| `NFS` | [`yba_nfs_storage_config`](nfs_storage_config) |

Migration steps for an S3 storage config (other backends are analogous):

1. Replace the `yba_storage_config_resource` block with the typed resource and lift the nested credential block:

    ```hcl
    # Before (deprecated)
    resource "yba_storage_config_resource" "s3" {
      name            = "S3"
      config_name     = "my-s3-config"
      backup_location = "s3://my-bucket/yugabyte-backups"
      s3_credentials {
        access_key_id     = "<aws-access-key-id>"
        secret_access_key = "<aws-secret-access-key>"
      }
    }

    # After
    resource "yba_s3_storage_config" "s3" {
      name              = "my-s3-config"
      backup_location   = "s3://my-bucket/yugabyte-backups"
      access_key_id     = "<aws-access-key-id>"
      secret_access_key = "<aws-secret-access-key>"
    }
    ```

2. Move the existing resource state to the new address and re-import (state is not transferable across schemas):

    ```sh
    terraform state rm yba_storage_config_resource.s3
    terraform import yba_s3_storage_config.s3 <config-uuid>
    ```

3. Run `terraform plan` and reconcile any drift. The resource type itself replaces the old `name` field (backend code); the human-readable name moves from `config_name` to `name`. The typed resources drop the credential sub-blocks (`s3_credentials`, `gcs_credentials`, `azure_credentials`) and promote their fields to the top level.

See the individual typed resource pages for the full schema and additional examples (e.g. IAM, workload identity, custom NFS bucket).

## Import

Storage configurations can be imported using `storage configuration uuid`:

```sh
terraform import yba_storage_config_resource.storage_config <storage configuration uuid>
```
